| publisher=Life magazine
| date=1944-05-22
| quote=Being now abreast of this island, the extremity ending in a beautiful clump of trees, I hauled up to look at the bay.  It appeared to be safe and commodious, sheltered by a long reef running parallel with the island, with two large inlets into the bay.  The reef is about 3/4 of a mile from the beach, and has several small islands which appear like flower pots.
